PROJECT: Odoo 19 + Mobile API (Cloud, production-critical)

ABSOLUTE PRIORITY
A bug in any mobile API endpoint MUST NOT crash or stop the Odoo service.

MANDATORY RULES
1) Every HTTP controller MUST wrap logic in try/except Exception
   - Always return JSON
   - Never allow unhandled exceptions
   - Never return recordsets or Python objects

2) Every response MUST follow this shape:
   {
     success: boolean,
     code: string,
     message: string,
     request_id: string,
     data: object | null,
     meta: object | null
   }

3) Every request MUST generate request_id (uuid4)
   - request_id MUST appear in:
     - response JSON
     - server logs
     - error logs with full traceback

4) Validate ALL inputs before ORM:
   - required fields
   - types
   - bounds (limit <= 50, qty <= 999, etc.)
   - invalid input → 400 JSON (VALIDATION_ERROR)

5) ORM SAFETY:
   - No unbounded search/search_read
   - Always use limit/offset for list endpoints
   - Avoid N+1 ORM loops
   - Never load binary/image fields in list endpoints

6) Access control:
   - Do NOT use sudo() unless explicitly justified
   - When using sudo(), restrict domain + fields

7) Add kill-switch support:
   - ir.config_parameter: api_disabled:/api/v1/xxx
   - If disabled → return 503 JSON

8) No heavy logic in controllers
   - Move business logic to service layer
   - Controllers should only orchestrate

WORKFLOW (MANDATORY)
A) Identify root cause and failure type
B) Patch with safety + validation
C) Provide smoke test (curl)
D) Provide restart/upgrade commands

OUTPUT REQUIREMENTS
- Show file paths changed
- Show minimal patch snippets
- Provide 3–5 curl test commands
